                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/561</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Denmark</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_EMF1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Egan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-17T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1917, noon</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 6.35 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>591. Germany offering higher and higher bids for peace to Russia. Cadet Party
                    which has seized the revolutionary movement <pb facs="0101" n="27"
                        xml:id="pg_27"/> unable to hold out against workingmen’s association. If the
                    United States could give Russia some tangible evidence that it is really in the
                    war such as a technical corps sent to Russia from the United States or the
                    announcement of some special assistance the separate peace proposals might be
                    nullified. Foreign Minister here believes that peace in July is possible; he is
                    influenced by socialistic opinion. <persName>Baron Buxhöveden</persName>,
                    Russian Minister here, has been dismissed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_EMF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Egan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
